        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 11:14AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1114 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Hardin, or 10 miles southwest of Thicket, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Livingston, Shepherd, Hardin, Plum Grove, Kenefick,
Goodrich, North Cleveland, Dayton Lakes, Tarkington Prairie, Segno,
Moss Hill, Romayor, and Rye.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
